<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="482" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,645,1390]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,717,742]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">Description.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation box="[438,525,717,742]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 20" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1874,1897]" captionTargetBox="[187,1351,203,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[171,1415,193,1836]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 20. Adults of Kiwaia (Empista) spp. 11, K. (E.) septentrionala sp. n., PT, ♀ (China: Shanxi); 12, K. (E.) septentrionala sp. n., PT, ♀ (China: Shanxi); 13, K. (E.) septentrionala sp. n., PT, ♂ (China: Gansu); 14, K. (E.) centrica sp. n., HT, ♂ (China: Hunan); 15, K. (E.) centrica sp. n., PT, ♀ (China: Hunan); 16, K. (E.) centrica sp. n., ♀ (China: Gansu); 17, K. (E.) spinosa (Povolný), HT, ♂ (Nepal); 18, K. (E.) montana sp. n., HT, ♂ (China: Xizang); 19, K. (E.) montana sp. n., PT, ♂ (China: Xizang); 20, K. (E.) medogia sp. n., HT, ♂ (China: Xizang)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265644/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">
Fig. 
<number box="[494,525,718,742]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
): Wingspan 14.0 mm. Head, thorax and tegulae grey mixed with black, frons lighter, grey; labial palpus up-curved, brown with white medial and apical belts, inner surface of segment 
<number box="[1362,1376,754,778]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482" value="2.0">2</number>
light grey, segment 
<number box="[320,334,790,814]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482" value="3.0">3</number>
about 1.5 times shorter and 1.5 times narrower than segment 
<number box="[1066,1083,790,814]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482" value="2.0">2</number>
; scapus brown, other antennal segments brown with white rings; forewing grey, costal margin black, black dash under 
<number box="[1151,1161,826,850]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1171,1187,826,850]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482" value="4.0">4</number>
of costal margin, two diffuse black spots and black dash near base in mid-width, black spot near base of dorsal margin, diffuse black pattern from 
<number box="[300,310,898,922]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[321,335,898,922]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482" value="3.0">3</number>
to about one half length in cell, two black dots in the middle of cell, apical area weakly mottled with black; cilia grey black tipped; hindwing light grey.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,645,1390]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[380,467,969,994]" captionStart="FIGURES 42 – 47" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1919,1942]" captionTargetBox="[163,1418,213,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 42 – 47. Male genitalia of Kiwaia (Empista) spp. 42, K. (E.) centrica sp. n., HT (China: Hunan), slide no. SYW 05204; 43, K. (E.) centrica sp. n., PT (China: Hunan), slide no. SYW 05224; 44, K. (E.) spinosa (Povolný), HT (Nepal), slide Jp. 4833; 45, K. (E.) montana sp. n., HT (China: Xizang), slide no. L 07029; 46, K. (E.) montana sp. n., PT (China: Xizang), slide no. L 13017; 47 K. (E.) medogia sp. n., HT (China: Xizang), slide no. L 07038." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265648/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">
Fig. 
<number box="[434,467,970,994]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482" value="44.0">44</number>
</figureCitation>
): Uncus twice longer than broad on base, gradually narrowed, posterior margin with small medial incision; gnathos weakly curved, rather stout; tegumen nearly parallel-sided, anteromedial emargination deeply rounded; valva moderately broad, about of equal width, tapers into long thorn, not reaching the middle of uncus; sacculus broad, weakly curved inwards, 
<number box="[849,859,1078,1102]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[870,884,1078,1102]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482" value="3.0">3</number>
as long as valva; vinculum slightly broader than long, posteromedial emargination broad, vincular processes broadly rounded, covered apically with dense hairs and rare spines; saccus stout, broad; phallus nearly straight, caecum weakly inflated, top rounded, apical arm well developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,645,1390]" box="[199,400,1221,1246]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
