<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="482" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,645,1390]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1293,1318]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">Remarks.</emphasis>
As far as one can judge after the slightly worn 
<typeStatus box="[866,964,1293,1318]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">holotype</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName box="[973,1145,1294,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Kiwaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosa" subGenus="Empista">
<emphasis box="[973,999,1294,1317]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">K.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1017,1041,1294,1317]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">E.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1059,1145,1294,1317]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">spinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be most related externally to 
<taxonomicName box="[297,466,1329,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Kiwaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kostjuki" subGenus="Empista">
<emphasis box="[297,323,1330,1353]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">K.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[339,363,1330,1353]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">E.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[379,466,1329,1354]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">kostjuki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(for differences see under that species). The male genitalia can easily be recognized by the narrow prolonged uncus and the apically tapered valva.
</paragraph>
